    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** headlining the roster, carrying an elite 83.29 score. His matchup against Burke is the strongest of the day, bolstered by a 14% platoon advantage and a premium lead-off spot. Following closely is **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56), who benefits significantly from the matchup against McGreevy; his dynamic platoon edge and second-spot placement make him a near-automatic start. In the outfield, **Jackson Merrill** (70.83) is a vital tactical play. While his base projection is moderate, he gains a critical 2% efficiency boost from the slow delivery of Keller, which significantly increases his stolen base potential\u2014an essential consideration given our emphasis on the scarcest 5x5 category. Similarly, **Josh Lowe** (63.00) and **Kyle Tucker** (64.03) are strong starts; **Josh Lowe** captures a massive 14% platoon boost, while **Kyle Tucker** remains locked in due to his elite 0.372 xwOBA, despite the tough matchup against Cease.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, whose 50.94 score barely missed the cutoff. Despite his high base projection, he is penalized heavily by a negative 19% adjustment due to the elite 2.67 xERA of Ohtani. We elected to prioritize the higher-upside platoon matchups of **Nasim Nunez** and **Jacob Wilson** to maximize our daily efficiency floor. We are exercising caution with **Luis Robert Jr.** (48.72), as his score has dipped due to a 15% negative platoon adjustment against Nelson; however, his presence in the starting lineup remains conditional on his ability to leverage his speed. We are closely monitoring the risk profile of **Andy Pages**, who faces Cease in a tough matchup that limits his ceiling. With no major weather concerns reported, the primary risk remains the high-caliber arms of Cease and Ohtani, which threaten to depress the counting stats for any of our hitters facing them today.",
